Both required outputs are in place:

- **`transcript.json`** (66 KB): 14 iterations with 54 hypotheses and 138 analyses. Schema-validated. Covers main effects, treatment main effects, biomarker effects, lab correlates, smoking/histology, targeted-therapy × biomarker interactions, pembrolizumab heterogeneity, multivariable adjustment, joint subgroups, comprehensive interaction screen, CART subgroup discovery, refined sotorasib subgroup search, confirmatory triple interaction, and final subgroup hypotheses for each treatment.

- **`analysis_summary.txt`**: Iteration-by-iteration narrative of the findings.

**Headline finding:** The only drug-biomarker pair with a robust PFS benefit in this cohort is **sotorasib in KRAS G12C+ males** (~+4.6 mo PFS, p ≈ 0; three-way sotorasib × KRAS × sex interaction p = 3.6e-83). The benefit is essentially absent in KRAS+ females and absent in KRAS- patients of either sex. Osimertinib×EGFR, olaparib×BRCA2, and pembrolizumab×PD-L1/TMB/STK11/smoking all return null interactions in this dataset. Strong baseline-feature effects on PFS include age (positive), ECOG, stage IV, brain mets, albumin, weight loss, and histology.
